      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027ll defer addressing other comments before we figure out whether we should use string or []rune.\n\nThe reason I choose rune over string while I was implementing this is that \n1. we may be dealing with non-ASCII characters so converting it to []rune means that while iterating, we will iterate over character instead of all bytes a unicode code point is encoded to. \n2. it allow me to leverage some helper function unicode pkg provides like `isDigit` or `isLetter` which I don\u0027t find it available for byte.\n\nNow that I read more I realize that those conversion may introduce extra overhead (e.g. mem allocation) and also incur more copies as you pointed out in the comment. So, for the sake of performance, now I am more lean towards using string directly. Is that also what you suggested?",
