      "side": 1,
      "message": "1. yes, i understand that we might need to deal with unicode. Yet, this problem is not at all parsing-specific. It is a generic problem for the entire Golang and yet, golang made a choice to use operate on \"string\" in all libraries and very few operate on []rune. This should be a sign for us that we are solving this problem differently from everyone else.\n2. i feel like you are assuming that dealing with \"string\" type necessarily means that we operate on raw bytes.  Have you read https://blog.golang.org/strings ? It explains how range loop iterates over runes, and how utf8.DecodeRuneInString can be used to read a rune.\n\nyes, i recommend using string directly, and then use range-loop, utf8 package and unicide package to extract runes when you need. WDYT?",
